{"key":"post-9498275","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9498275</id>\n<content>First of all, it's manure, not shit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Rye is a spawn material, manure is a bulk substrate.&amp;nbsp; Your best use of your spawn is to mix it at a ratio of anywhere from even to 1:4 with the manure.&amp;nbsp; The resulting mix is what you'll fruit.&amp;nbsp; Whether you make a few layers of each, or mix thoroughly matters little, but don't use a 3&quot; layer of rye and a 1&quot; layer of manure.&amp;nbsp; Use more manure than that, and a couple of trays of alternating 1/2&quot; layers of each, stacked several layers thick will deliver more bang for the buck.&amp;nbsp; Be sure to have manure as the top layer.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9498499</next>\n<prev>9498142</prev>\n<first>9497520</first>\n<last>9499445</last>\n<when>1230334616</when>\n<utime>12/27/08 01:36 AM</utime>\n</post>"}